The paper deals with distributed optimization problems in peer-to-peer networks, which involves algorithms and techniques from distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on robustness against communication or processor failures suggests a connection to control theory (cs.SY). The use of linear programming and polyhedral approximations suggests a connection to mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the application examples in wireless sensor networks and microgrid control suggest a connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
